dct_title_s: Iberian Peninsula 1:250,000: Salamanca, sheet 39. Series A.M.S. M581
dct_description_sm: United States. Army Map Service. North Decimal Degree 41.0000. South Decimal Degree 40.0000. East Decimal Degree -5.0000. West Decimal Degree -6.0000. Alternate title: Salamanca, Spain. Polyconic projection. With Spanish-English glossary. Relief shown by 100 m. contour interval, gradient tint and spot heights. Standard map series designation: A.M.S. M581. "Compiled from Spain, 1:50,000, Instituto Geografico, undated and 1934-42; Spain, 1:200,000, Instituto Geografico, PROVINCIA DE AVILA, 1930, PROVINCIA DE CACERES, 1922, PROVINCIA DE TOLEDO, 1935; Spain 1:200,000, Cuartel General del Generalisimo, 1916-36; Iberian Peninsula, 1:250,000, GSGS sheets S3648, 3656 and S3664, 1941; Spain & Portugal Road Map, 1:400,000, AMS, sheets 44 and 46, Third Edition, 1943; Railways in Spain and Portugal 1:1,500,000, GSGS, 1941, corrected from Intelligence Reports, 1942-44. Partially revised from aerial photography, 1943.".
